---

The critical insight here: **`overflow: hidden` on a section clips everything that overflows it — including the fixed-position background canvas that lives outside the DOM hierarchy.** Fixed elements are positioned relative to the viewport, not their parent — but `overflow: hidden` on any ancestor still clips them in some browsers (especially Chrome). Removing it and using `clip-path: inset(0)` on the content instead is the correct architectural fix — it clips only the text, never the background.
